Greetings, David!

I've been assigned as Judge in this CFJ, which alleges that you broke
Rule 1497.  I have received your argument posted subsequently in 
the Public Forum; thank you.  It is relevant to ask your state of 
mind when you posted the following message:

> Date: Wed, 8 Nov 95 09:36:09 EST
> From: "David M. Chess" <chess@watson.ibm.com>
> To: nomic-business@teleport.com
> Subject: BUS: Apothecary's Romance
> 
> I hereby cause 217 Extra Votes to be created and transferred
> to me.  I hereby cause the right to cast up to nine votes
> on any and all Proposals to be granted to me.
> 
> Gad, what a feeling of power!   *8)
> 
> | favor |

I invite you to give evidence on this matter.  Specifically, when you
posted the message, which is it most accurate to say: 

   A)  you believed that you thereby caused the actions mentioned,
 
   B)  you disbelieved this,
or
   C)  you posted the statements without believing or disbelieving this,
       that is without regard to the truth of the statements.

If I've missed a possibility please let me know.

Regards,
- elJefe, Judge

